WEBVTT

00:09.750 --> 00:10.999
(Music playing)

00:11.000 --> 00:12.666
- (sighs)
- <i>(knock on door)</i>

00:12.667 --> 00:15.125
Man: <i>We're ready for you, Mr. President.</i>

00:16.833 --> 00:18.999
Oh, fuck.

00:19.000 --> 00:22.291
Man #2: <i>"One of a kind"
doesn't come close.</i>

00:22.755 --> 00:24.207
There's no one like him.

00:24.208 --> 00:29.332
Never has been,
and I doubt there ever will be.

00:29.723 --> 00:34.786
So, along with former Governor
of New Mexico Bill Richardson

00:34.787 --> 00:37.812
and the great Mayor of
New York Rudy Giuliani,

00:38.246 --> 00:40.760
it is my honor to present to you

00:40.908 --> 00:45.472
our two-term former President
of the United States,

00:45.473 --> 00:47.241
- Richard Graves.
- (applause)

00:47.242 --> 00:50.907
♪ Please allow me to introduce myself ♪

00:50.908 --> 00:55.657
♪ I'm a man of wealth and taste ♪

00:55.658 --> 00:56.992
♪ I've been around... ♪

00:56.993 --> 00:59.158
Thank you, sir.

00:59.159 --> 01:01.074
This veterans' home

01:01.075 --> 01:04.532
is the very least our government can do

01:04.533 --> 01:09.657
to provide a home for those who
were willing to lose their lives

01:09.658 --> 01:12.379
to guarantee our freedoms.

01:13.408 --> 01:14.995
So, God bless you all.

01:14.996 --> 01:16.941
♪ Pleased to meet you ♪

01:16.942 --> 01:19.867
♪ Hope you guessed my name ♪

01:21.950 --> 01:24.116
♪ But what's puzzling you ♪

01:24.117 --> 01:28.200
- <i>♪ Is the nature of my game ♪</i>
- Three, two, one.

01:31.575 --> 01:34.780
♪ Stuck around St. Petersburg ♪

01:34.781 --> 01:37.116
♪ <i>When I saw it was a time ♪</i>

01:37.117 --> 01:38.450
Graves: <i>What do you want, Walsh?</i>

01:38.451 --> 01:40.449
Well, the RPEC conference

01:40.450 --> 01:42.074
is meeting in a couple of months

01:42.075 --> 01:43.950
and we're gonna honor you,
Mr. President...

01:43.951 --> 01:47.223
the last great Republican
to sit in the Oval Office.

01:47.224 --> 01:50.157
Now, can I convince you to attend?

01:50.158 --> 01:52.241
Honor me when I'm dead.

01:52.242 --> 01:54.907
25 years out of office

01:54.908 --> 01:58.617
and still no one packs in the
party faithful like you do, sir.

01:58.618 --> 02:00.407
I couldn't care less.

02:00.408 --> 02:03.679
Mr. President, I don't understand
why you're so hard on yourself.

02:03.680 --> 02:06.179
Did you read that article
in Slate online?

02:06.180 --> 02:09.532
"Richard Graves: Worst President
in U.S. History."

02:09.532 --> 02:13.241
Says you beat James Buchanan,
and he dissolved the union.

02:13.242 --> 02:15.199
Fuck you, Richardson.

02:15.200 --> 02:18.282
(All chuckling)

02:18.283 --> 02:21.782
Hey, driver, could you
pull it over for a minute?

02:21.783 --> 02:23.325
This'll just take a second.

02:23.326 --> 02:27.699
♪ Let me, please, introduce myself ♪

02:27.700 --> 02:31.408
♪ I'm a man of wealth and taste ♪

02:33.033 --> 02:35.866
♪ I laid traps for troubadours ♪

02:35.867 --> 02:38.074
♪ Who get killed before ♪
♪ they reach Bombay... ♪

02:38.075 --> 02:39.935
Worst president.

02:40.660 --> 02:41.701
Huh.

02:41.950 --> 02:43.430
Don't pay attention to Bill.

02:43.431 --> 02:45.535
Graves: <i>That's why I don't go online.</i>

02:45.536 --> 02:47.235
Opinions are like assholes...

02:47.288 --> 02:49.413
everybody's got one
and they always stink.

02:49.414 --> 02:52.226
All you can do is your best,
and you did.

02:52.227 --> 02:54.037
What's done is done...

02:54.522 --> 02:56.454
for all of us.

02:56.455 --> 02:59.829
♪ Aw, yeah, get down, baby... ♪

02:59.830 --> 03:01.708
(window whirring)

03:01.709 --> 03:05.121
I'm not dead yet! Go!

03:07.288 --> 03:10.330
Hey, hey!

03:13.038 --> 03:15.491
What a prick.

