- Hi.
- May I help you, sir?

03:46.830 --> 03:48.787
Yes, I'm here to see President Graves.

03:48.788 --> 03:50.871
I'm Isaiah Miller, his new assistant.

03:53.663 --> 03:56.995
(laughs)

03:56.996 --> 04:01.455
Uh, okay, go ahead.

04:08.163 --> 04:11.019
- Michael Steele called again.
- Oh, good. I'll call him later.

04:12.411 --> 04:14.620
Isaiah Miller.

04:14.996 --> 04:16.713
I hope you're ready for this.

04:16.738 --> 04:19.161
I have never been more ready to do
anything in my life, ma'am.

04:19.163 --> 04:21.786
- It is so nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

04:21.788 --> 04:24.859
You come highly recommended by
my friends at the Cato Institute.

04:24.860 --> 04:26.954
They wouldn't stop singing your praises.

04:26.955 --> 04:28.688
Well, for the record, ma'am,
I just want you to know

04:28.746 --> 04:30.829
that President Graves has been
the single seminal influence

04:30.830 --> 04:32.454
on my political and worldview.

04:32.455 --> 04:34.787
- I mean, his presidency...
- Don't do that.

04:34.788 --> 04:38.079
Don't romanticize. This isn't fun.

04:38.080 --> 04:39.538
- Oh.
- <i>(door opens)</i>

04:39.539 --> 04:41.787
Graves: <i>Never again, Maggie.</i>

04:41.788 --> 04:43.245
Never.

04:43.246 --> 04:45.662
- Maggie.
- Hey, darling.

04:45.663 --> 04:48.787
No more appearances
with political types.

04:48.788 --> 04:52.829
It is so, so goddamn depressing.

04:53.369 --> 04:54.815
Who's this?

04:54.859 --> 04:57.243
This is your new
assistant Isaiah Miller.

04:57.243 --> 04:59.662
It is such an extreme honor
to meet you, sir.

04:59.663 --> 05:03.662
Maggie, I do not need
any more assistants.

05:03.663 --> 05:06.395
I can wipe my own ass.

05:07.750 --> 05:09.830
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

05:12.496 --> 05:13.995
Wipe his ass? Does he really need...

05:13.996 --> 05:15.788
- Figure of speech.
- Right, of course.

05:15.789 --> 05:17.787
- Speech, right.
- I think.

05:17.788 --> 05:23.662
(Graves urinating, moaning)

05:24.516 --> 05:27.287
- That's an intimidating stream.
- Like a horse.

05:27.288 --> 05:29.687
Sweetheart, there's no way
you can survive your schedule

05:29.712 --> 05:32.244
without an assistant.
Your week is packed.

05:32.988 --> 05:34.995
And Isaiah has your itinerary.

05:34.996 --> 05:37.051
Yeah, yeah.

05:39.413 --> 05:41.767
- What's next?
- You fly to Texas today...

05:41.768 --> 05:44.474
Children's Health Initiative
sponsored by the White House.

05:44.475 --> 05:46.495
Just a fun day with some kids.

05:46.496 --> 05:48.162
Mags, that sounds like torture.

05:48.163 --> 05:50.162
And don't forget, we have
New York in two days...

05:50.163 --> 05:51.745
your Cancer Society keynote.

05:51.746 --> 05:53.955
Lawrence is gonna fly out
and help you with your speech.

05:53.956 --> 05:56.995
I'm like some old relic in storage

05:56.996 --> 06:00.620
that you wheel out once a
year, year after year.

06:00.621 --> 06:03.037
- Oh, Maggie.
- What, angel?

06:03.038 --> 06:06.162
- Will it ever end?
- Yes, it will, dear.

06:06.163 --> 06:09.436
But for now, I need you
to be nice to Isaiah.

06:10.121 --> 06:11.554
Who?

06:11.654 --> 06:13.501
Isaiah.

06:13.828 --> 06:15.084
Hi.

06:18.913 --> 06:21.912
(Woman singing in Spanish)

06:21.913 --> 06:24.454
How are you, President Graves?

06:24.455 --> 06:26.995
Pain, Ramona. Nothing but pain.

06:26.996 --> 06:28.467
That's good.

06:28.871 --> 06:31.434
I'll be gone for one day
to a book signing in Denver.

06:31.435 --> 06:32.892
- Yes, ma'am.
- I want you to...

06:32.893 --> 06:35.892
Mrs. Graves, you need
to see this before we go.

06:35.893 --> 06:39.059
As we reported earlier,
news of former first daughter

06:39.060 --> 06:41.205
Olivia Graves' marriage dissolution

06:41.206 --> 06:44.662
has been confirmed
by senior GOP leadership staff,

06:44.663 --> 06:47.120
where her husband serves
as a second-term congressman.

06:47.121 --> 06:50.371
The daughter of transformational
former President Richard Graves

06:50.372 --> 06:52.662
and iconic First Lady Margaret,

06:52.663 --> 06:55.537
Olivia is American political royalty.

06:55.538 --> 06:59.287
Get me Jacob. Then Olivia.

06:59.288 --> 07:01.184
Wolf Blitzer: <i>Little Livy,
as she was known...</i>

07:01.185 --> 07:03.351
worshipped by a generation of girls...

07:03.352 --> 07:07.329
is a long way from the fairy tale
White House she grew up in.

07:07.330 --> 07:09.995
I'm fine, Mother.

07:09.996 --> 07:12.684
Really, I'm just ridiculously fantastic.

07:12.685 --> 07:14.162
Margaret: <i>Oh, that tone.</i>

07:14.163 --> 07:16.934
What are you doing right now,
right this second?

07:17.352 --> 07:19.060
Right now I just finished
blowtorching the hell

07:19.060 --> 07:21.038
out of William's Queen Anne table,

07:21.039 --> 07:23.329
the one the Smithsonian wanted,

07:23.781 --> 07:25.329
among other things.

07:25.330 --> 07:28.412
Do me a favor
and leave me the hell alone.

07:28.413 --> 07:30.495
Don't be here for me.

07:30.496 --> 07:32.944
Don't understand.

07:32.969 --> 07:36.287
Livy, this is a trigger.
Don't you purge.

07:36.288 --> 07:40.162
I was bulimic for, like,
a day when I was 15, Mother.

07:40.163 --> 07:43.870
Literally one fucking day!

07:43.871 --> 07:47.245
Okay, you do not handle stress well,
honey. You need to come home.

07:47.246 --> 07:48.786
Olivia: <i>Oh, my God.</i>

07:48.787 --> 07:52.829
(sobbing) I loved him so much.

07:52.830 --> 07:54.299
Oh.

07:54.705 --> 07:56.955
- Man: <i>Olivia?
- (knock on door)</i>

08:00.084 --> 08:01.995
You sent Uncle Jacob?

08:02.416 --> 08:04.870
I don't need your fucking fixer!

08:04.871 --> 08:07.162
You listen to Uncle Jacob.

08:08.183 --> 08:11.163
Livy, put the blowtorch down, honey.

08:11.900 --> 08:15.912
Sweetheart, give me the blowtorch.

08:15.913 --> 08:20.662
♪ Are you looking for an answer? ♪

08:20.663 --> 08:22.705
♪ Are you looking for an answer? ♪

08:22.706 --> 08:23.955
Shh, shh, shh.

08:27.496 --> 08:29.455
I'm sorry.

08:33.996 --> 08:36.955
Take Richard into town
before you fly to Texas.

08:36.956 --> 08:38.995
He needs to see people.

08:38.996 --> 08:40.828
He needs a dose of adoration.

08:40.830 --> 08:43.455
It's the only thing that's gonna shake
him out of this pissy mood he's in.

08:43.456 --> 08:46.245
Yes, ma'am. This is so exciting.

08:46.596 --> 08:47.996
You poor thing.

08:51.322 --> 08:52.970
Isaiah: Just to get it out of the way,
I have to tell you

08:52.995 --> 08:54.767
how exciting this is for me, sir.

08:54.768 --> 08:56.351
Honestly, your presidency serves

08:56.352 --> 08:59.080
- as the conservative model...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

08:59.081 --> 09:01.162
Hello, hello. God bless you.

09:01.163 --> 09:03.162
- Hello. Hello.
- Woman: Hi, Mr. President.

09:03.163 --> 09:04.726
God bless you. God bless you.

09:04.727 --> 09:06.454
Hey, hi. How are you doing?

09:06.455 --> 09:07.829
Bless you. God bless you.

09:07.830 --> 09:09.829
Good to see you. I miss you, too.

09:09.830 --> 09:12.120
I miss you all.

09:12.121 --> 09:13.996
God bless you!

09:16.746 --> 09:18.195
Hello, hello.

09:18.621 --> 09:20.403
Morning, guys.

09:20.956 --> 09:23.830
- Where's Sylvia?
- She retired last week.

09:23.830 --> 09:26.495
- What, already?
- She was 87.

09:26.496 --> 09:27.912
Oh. Oh.

09:27.913 --> 09:30.413
- Coffee?
- Yes, please.

09:31.830 --> 09:34.704
I'm Richard Graves.

09:34.705 --> 09:36.412
Samantha.

09:36.413 --> 09:37.995
- Sammy.
- Sammy.

09:37.996 --> 09:41.745
- This boy is...
- Isaiah. Isaiah Miller.

09:41.746 --> 09:43.267
President Graves' assistant.

09:43.268 --> 09:44.662
First time saying that.

09:44.663 --> 09:48.120
President? Oh, shit, that's right.

09:48.121 --> 09:49.995
I knew I recognized you
from somewhere, man,

09:49.996 --> 09:54.495
but, honestly, I kind of
thought you were dead.

09:54.883 --> 09:57.580
Is that Latin?

09:57.580 --> 09:58.662
Oh, yeah.

09:58.663 --> 10:01.870
Amor Vincit Omnia?

10:01.871 --> 10:04.579
Love conquers all things.

10:04.580 --> 10:05.922
Right.

10:06.330 --> 10:07.995
Bit simplistic.

10:07.996 --> 10:09.870
Well, I'm a fan of simple.

10:09.871 --> 10:11.699
Oh? All right.

10:12.147 --> 10:14.581
Well, I will be right back to
take your order, Mr. President.

10:14.581 --> 10:16.203
Thank you.

10:17.748 --> 10:20.330
What the hell are you staring at?

10:28.580 --> 10:30.162
You got any Latino in you?

10:30.863 --> 10:32.370
Actually, I do, in fact, yes.

10:32.371 --> 10:36.995
Mayan? Where's your family from?
Chiapas? Yucatán?

10:36.996 --> 10:39.537
Uh, no, my... well, my dad...

10:39.538 --> 10:41.892
Yucatec Maya's a beautiful language.

10:41.893 --> 10:44.413
- Oh.
- I've heard it spoken only once.

10:44.414 --> 10:48.995
I was on a diplomatic summit with
President Portillo of Mexico,

10:48.996 --> 10:52.912
and I was sitting on top of a pyramid

10:52.913 --> 10:55.245
in the middle of a jungle.

10:56.219 --> 10:59.496
Actually, I'm half Spanish,
half German Jew, sir.

10:59.967 --> 11:03.509
From St. Louis, originally,
but then my mom moved us to Phoenix

11:03.510 --> 11:05.929
when I was four, a state
which you carried two times.

11:05.954 --> 11:08.269
Obviously, you know that, though.

11:08.694 --> 11:12.287
Anyone ever tell you what
a goddamn buzzkill you are?

11:12.542 --> 11:14.870
Uh, yeah.

11:14.871 --> 11:16.829
(Bell rings)

11:16.830 --> 11:18.909
Woman: <i>All right, here we go!
Looking good!</i>

11:18.910 --> 11:21.245
Don't stop, keep it up. You got this.

11:21.246 --> 11:22.829
Nobody quits today.

11:22.830 --> 11:24.829
Nobody's giving up on me.

11:24.830 --> 11:26.370
Nobody's gonna stop.

11:26.371 --> 11:29.120
- She's the devil.
- <i>Stick with it.</i>

11:29.121 --> 11:30.495
How does it feel, Mr. President?

11:30.496 --> 11:34.829
- Feels good, right?
- A life lived healthy

11:34.830 --> 11:37.704
is a life worthwhile, kids.

11:37.705 --> 11:39.267
Did you hear that, guys?

11:39.268 --> 11:41.288
That's a former President
of the United States,

11:41.289 --> 11:44.329
and if he can do it, you can do it.

11:44.330 --> 11:45.912
10 more. That's it.

11:45.913 --> 11:47.662
You're doing great, sir.

11:47.663 --> 11:49.829
- Great.
- Motherfucker.

11:49.830 --> 11:53.745
Three, two, one. Awesome job, everybody.

11:53.746 --> 11:55.204
Awesome job.

11:55.205 --> 11:57.745
I'm in hell.

11:57.746 --> 12:00.412
I've died and been sent to hell.

12:00.413 --> 12:02.538
Huh?

12:15.705 --> 12:17.037
(Sighs)

12:17.038 --> 12:20.412
♪ I don't want to work away ♪

12:20.413 --> 12:23.579
♪ Doing just what they all say ♪

12:23.871 --> 12:27.412
♪ Work hard, boy, you'll find ♪

12:27.413 --> 12:30.745
♪ One day you'll have a job like mine ♪

12:30.746 --> 12:34.162
♪ 'Cause I know for sure ♪

12:34.163 --> 12:37.787
♪ Nobody should be that poor ♪

12:37.788 --> 12:41.162
♪ Say yes or sink below ♪

12:41.163 --> 12:44.870
♪ Because you happen to say so, say so ♪

12:44.871 --> 12:46.620
♪ You say so ♪

