13:47.788 --> 13:49.662
President Graves?

13:49.663 --> 13:51.621
Bring your car around in back.

13:51.622 --> 13:53.454
We're slipping out today.

13:54.578 --> 13:56.954
But, sir, what about
your Secret Service detail?

13:57.681 --> 14:00.403
Fuck 'em.
Are you in?

14:02.121 --> 14:04.636
What... what is this?

14:04.637 --> 14:06.412
Hazing the pledge.

14:06.413 --> 14:09.329
Been doing it since
my Theta Beta Phi days.

14:09.330 --> 14:11.329
Wear the letters for two days

14:11.330 --> 14:13.038
without washing them off.

14:13.039 --> 14:16.320
Show me I can trust you.

14:16.911 --> 14:20.495
- Can you do that?
- Yeah, yeah, you can trust me, sir.

14:20.496 --> 14:21.870
Oh, good.

14:21.871 --> 14:23.745
Now, don't be an asshole.

14:23.746 --> 14:26.287
Bring your car around back, okay?

14:26.288 --> 14:29.162
♪ I pulled into Nazareth ♪

14:29.163 --> 14:30.413
♪ Was feelin' about half past dead... ♪

14:30.414 --> 14:32.434
So, where exactly am I going?

14:32.435 --> 14:36.954
Take the 85 to the I-40.
I'll tell you from there.

14:37.553 --> 14:39.871
Uh, I wanted to show you this, sir.

14:39.871 --> 14:41.621
♪ Hey, mister, can you tell me... ♪

14:41.622 --> 14:44.412
That's me.
I was one of those babies

14:44.413 --> 14:46.434
that you kissed at a campaign stop.

14:46.435 --> 14:48.517
My mom, she always loved you, sir.

14:48.518 --> 14:51.746
She worked the Graves
for President office in Phoenix

14:51.747 --> 14:53.829
and worked door to door.

14:54.112 --> 14:57.329
See, my dad, he left before I was born,

14:57.330 --> 15:01.495
so growing up, when things got tough,

15:01.496 --> 15:04.621
I always came back to that
picture of you holding me up.

15:05.955 --> 15:07.787
That's the fattest goddamn baby

15:07.788 --> 15:09.855
I think I've ever seen.

15:10.913 --> 15:13.495
I had a bit of a thyroid problem, yes.

15:13.496 --> 15:15.749
A bit?

15:16.163 --> 15:18.037
♪ ...it's time ♪

15:18.038 --> 15:20.495
♪ To get back to Miss Fannie ♪

15:20.496 --> 15:24.995
♪ You know she's the only one ♪

15:24.996 --> 15:26.912
♪ Who sent me here ♪

15:26.913 --> 15:31.454
♪ With her regards for everyone ♪

15:31.455 --> 15:34.787
♪ Take a load off, Fannie... ♪

15:34.788 --> 15:37.995
Oh, wow. Your library, sir.
I've never been here before.

15:37.996 --> 15:39.455
Pull the car around back.

15:39.456 --> 15:41.912
♪ Take a load off, Fannie ♪

15:41.913 --> 15:44.454
♪ And, and, and ♪

15:44.455 --> 15:46.455
♪ You put the load right on me ♪

15:46.456 --> 15:48.746
♪ You put the load right on me ♪

15:59.413 --> 16:01.517
President Graves, what a pleasure.

16:01.518 --> 16:04.620
Afternoon, Freddie.
I'll just be a few minutes.

16:04.621 --> 16:07.829
Well, the museum is closed on Mondays,
so it's all yours.

16:07.830 --> 16:10.330
- Good.
- Thank you.

16:30.602 --> 16:32.315
Your son Jeremy.

16:32.360 --> 16:34.017
- He's in Kabul, isn't he?
- Yeah.

16:34.018 --> 16:35.301
You know, when I was a kid,

16:35.302 --> 16:38.352
Jeremy's national Scout
campaign really inspired me.

16:38.353 --> 16:40.329
I actually joined because of him.

16:40.330 --> 16:42.301
Got over 100 merit badges.

16:42.788 --> 16:46.302
124, to be exact. Sir?

16:49.725 --> 16:51.918
He shot me three times.

16:52.941 --> 16:55.580
The bullets went right on through.

16:57.246 --> 16:58.765
There it is.

17:00.501 --> 17:02.455
There it is.

17:31.455 --> 17:33.621
These were just kids...

17:36.080 --> 17:38.729
...and I sent 'em to be slaughtered.

17:40.209 --> 17:42.495
Just slaughtered.

17:42.496 --> 17:45.205
I don't even remember why.

17:46.288 --> 17:48.829
- Permission to speak?
- Yeah.

17:48.830 --> 17:52.620
You saved a lot of lives, sir, in Libya.

17:52.621 --> 17:54.495
During my debate class in 10th grade,

17:54.496 --> 17:58.591
I argued your preemptive action
was the only humane choice.

17:59.721 --> 18:01.512
It was genocide there.

18:01.746 --> 18:03.455
So was this.

18:04.996 --> 18:06.639
So was this.

18:07.580 --> 18:09.094
The guard.

18:09.371 --> 18:11.055
- Hmm?
- The guard.

18:11.621 --> 18:14.344
Talk to him. Take him outside.

18:14.996 --> 18:16.995
I need to be alone for a while.

18:16.996 --> 18:18.996
Oh, yeah. Okay.

18:24.996 --> 18:26.371
♪ Ooh, ooh, yeah ♪

18:28.996 --> 18:30.745
♪ Lookie here ♪

18:30.746 --> 18:33.705
♪ There's a secret place ♪
♪ that I go in my mind ♪

18:33.706 --> 18:35.454
♪ Where there's no trouble ♪

18:35.455 --> 18:38.120
♪ Where the pain gets left behind ♪

18:38.121 --> 18:39.954
♪ A place that I control ♪

18:39.955 --> 18:41.829
♪ All the thoughts that leave my soul... ♪

18:41.830 --> 18:43.120
Good afternoon, Charles.

18:43.121 --> 18:44.432
Sir.

18:45.339 --> 18:47.454
Ah, that old familiar smell

18:47.455 --> 18:48.934
of tumbleweeds and demoralization.

18:48.935 --> 18:50.162
Charles: <i>Yes, sir.</i>

18:50.163 --> 18:52.162
All right, where's the big guy?

18:52.163 --> 18:53.454
Mr. President, it's Lawrence.

18:53.455 --> 18:54.662
Thought we'd kick around

18:54.663 --> 18:56.112
the cancer speech for tomorrow.

18:58.121 --> 18:59.505
Sir?

19:01.330 --> 19:02.840
Ramona?

19:03.538 --> 19:06.162
♪ You gotta, you gotta, you gotta... ♪

19:06.163 --> 19:08.270
Ah, carajo.

19:10.413 --> 19:11.726
Get Mrs. Graves on the phone.

19:11.727 --> 19:13.329
- Loved it, man.
- It was beautiful.

19:13.330 --> 19:14.620
- Good to see you, Freddie.
- Huh?

19:14.621 --> 19:16.662
- Let's go, kid.
- What?

19:16.663 --> 19:18.705
♪ Steppa the fire, steppa the beat... ♪

19:18.706 --> 19:21.787
So, home now, I assume? I pray?

19:21.788 --> 19:24.495
Actually, not yet.

19:24.496 --> 19:27.162
♪ See how far you can see... ♪

19:27.163 --> 19:28.829
♪ Aw, baby ♪

19:28.830 --> 19:31.495
♪ You gotta, you gotta you gotta ♪

19:31.496 --> 19:34.912
- <i>♪ Higher and higher ♪</i>
- What the hell?

19:34.913 --> 19:39.662
♪ Push it higher and higher ♪

19:39.663 --> 19:41.829
♪ Can you feel it, babe? ♪

19:41.830 --> 19:43.829
♪ Go tell it on the mountain, babe... ♪

19:43.830 --> 19:47.079
Dispatch, I need a supervisor, ASAP.

19:47.080 --> 19:48.455
Dispatch: <i>Copy.</i>

19:50.663 --> 19:52.954
I don't know what
that library thing was about,

19:52.955 --> 19:54.684
but I am not okay right now.

19:54.685 --> 19:58.038
It is so late, and we have to
tell someone where you are.

19:58.039 --> 20:00.912
Hey, guys. You're back.

20:01.457 --> 20:03.246
I remembered something.

20:03.483 --> 20:05.009
May I?

20:05.733 --> 20:07.580
Oh, yeah. Go for it.

20:13.871 --> 20:15.162
Marijuana.

20:16.430 --> 20:17.956
No.

20:23.413 --> 20:26.412
I'm starting to think
that too much sanity

20:26.413 --> 20:29.038
is a form of insanity.

20:31.788 --> 20:34.370
This is so bad.

20:34.959 --> 20:36.329
What's up with pretty boy?

20:36.330 --> 20:38.287
- He's pissed off.
- Mm.

20:38.288 --> 20:40.537
Pissed? No, no, no, no.

20:40.538 --> 20:42.329
Freaking out? Well, yeah.

20:42.330 --> 20:43.579
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

20:43.580 --> 20:45.434
I'm sitting here at 3:00 AM

20:45.435 --> 20:47.454
with a former president,
my personal hero,

20:47.455 --> 20:51.454
who's smoking marijuana after we've
been off the grid for the entire day.

20:51.455 --> 20:53.164
And there is no version of that

20:53.165 --> 20:55.121
where I don't lose the job
that I've dreamt about

20:55.122 --> 20:56.204
since I was 10.

20:56.645 --> 20:58.787
I am really hungry.

20:59.541 --> 21:01.413
I don't think I've ever
been this hungry.

21:01.414 --> 21:04.037
Would you get me something to eat?

21:04.038 --> 21:05.767
Yeah... yes, sir, but where?

21:05.768 --> 21:07.538
Oh, there's munchies in my trailer.

21:07.539 --> 21:10.121
Oh, there's munch... there's munchies.

21:12.913 --> 21:15.412
(Playing tune)

21:15.946 --> 21:18.726
What have I been doing with my life

21:18.727 --> 21:22.829
for the last 20 or 30 years?

21:23.384 --> 21:25.616
You're way too much in your head.

21:26.336 --> 21:28.580
Where else am I to go?

21:29.080 --> 21:31.766
Anywhere. Just live authentically.
You're already doing it.

21:31.766 --> 21:34.995
You're out here getting high with
some random waitress you just met.

21:35.304 --> 21:37.163
There's no way that was on the books.

21:41.330 --> 21:43.384
I've done some really...

21:44.580 --> 21:48.295
really terrible things.

21:49.824 --> 21:51.580
Okay, so now you can go

21:51.580 --> 21:54.863
and you can do some really,
really good things.

21:55.404 --> 21:56.945
At my age?

21:57.746 --> 22:01.634
I don't think I have more
than five good years left.

22:02.698 --> 22:06.538
Five fucking awesome years.

22:13.330 --> 22:14.662
Jesus.

22:14.663 --> 22:16.371
Who would live in a place like this?

22:16.372 --> 22:19.787
People live here? All right.

22:19.788 --> 22:23.662
- (Dish clatters)
- So bad. This is filthy.

22:23.663 --> 22:25.163
All right, I got munchies!

22:28.246 --> 22:29.454
President Graves?

22:30.130 --> 22:32.662
Oh, no.
Oh, Jesus.

22:32.663 --> 22:33.954
(Car approaches)

22:33.955 --> 22:36.537
Oh, hey, excuse me. Hello. Hi, hi.

22:36.538 --> 22:39.059
Uh, sorry to bother you.
Funniest thing...

22:39.060 --> 22:40.767
actually not funny at all.

22:40.768 --> 22:43.662
Did you see a tall man in a
hoodie leave in my Prius?

22:44.429 --> 22:45.996
What the fuck is on your face?

22:45.996 --> 22:48.329
(laughing)

22:48.330 --> 22:50.121
Look, I need your help.

22:52.705 --> 22:55.101
So, who was this guy with Sammy again?

22:55.102 --> 22:58.434
Literally, the most consequential
person I could possibly lose.

22:58.435 --> 23:00.829
Hey, I lost a vintage Fender guitar

23:00.830 --> 23:02.913
at this strip club in Reno last summer.

23:02.914 --> 23:05.246
Not the same, Chaco. Trust me.

23:07.371 --> 23:09.788
- Thank you.
- <i>(men laughing)</i>

23:12.038 --> 23:14.495
Margaret: <i>One day.
I was gone for one day.</i>

23:14.496 --> 23:17.934
He ditched me, ma'am, at some
Manson Family trailer park.

23:17.935 --> 23:19.329
I don't even know what that means.

23:19.330 --> 23:20.858
He said it was part of the hazing,

23:20.883 --> 23:22.080
and then there was this
whole thing with the...

23:22.081 --> 23:24.995
Okay, okay. It's okay. What is this?

23:24.996 --> 23:27.329
Uh, oh, my God. I don't know.
I don't know!

23:28.638 --> 23:31.519
- Mommy.
- Angel.

23:31.913 --> 23:33.162
It's okay.

23:33.163 --> 23:35.120
Don't. Don't say anything.

23:35.886 --> 23:37.892
- Who the hell is this?
- I used to work here.

23:37.893 --> 23:40.162
Stop that. This is Daddy's
new assistant, Isaiah.

23:40.163 --> 23:41.287
Poor thing.

23:41.288 --> 23:42.495
Everyone keeps saying that.

23:42.496 --> 23:43.745
The damage?

23:43.746 --> 23:45.120
She blowtorched her way

23:45.121 --> 23:48.370
through 9.5 million worth
of antique furniture.

23:48.371 --> 23:50.579
- And?
- It's taken care of.

23:50.580 --> 23:52.287
- The Rockefellers...
- Can burn in hell.

23:52.288 --> 23:55.684
...are cooperating. They
want a clean, quiet divorce.

23:56.070 --> 23:58.120
What they want is
for him to be reelected,

23:58.121 --> 24:00.829
and we're gonna spin it around on them.

24:00.830 --> 24:02.851
Little Livy, America's princess,

24:02.852 --> 24:05.829
will not stand beside the
philandering man that shamed her.

24:05.830 --> 24:09.886
She's a strong, empowered young lady,

24:10.621 --> 24:12.260
and we're gonna make her the poster girl

24:12.261 --> 24:13.681
for the new emancipated woman.

24:13.682 --> 24:14.870
Hmm.

24:15.317 --> 24:17.077
I've always been such a disappointment.

24:17.156 --> 24:19.745
Oh, honey, no. Never say that.

24:20.289 --> 24:21.569
Have to go now, Maggie.

24:21.570 --> 24:24.246
It seems Big Bird
found his way to his library

24:24.247 --> 24:25.668
and did some redecorating.

24:26.080 --> 24:27.556
Oh, my God.

24:28.246 --> 24:29.871
Richard would never do this,

24:30.269 --> 24:32.370
not in a million years.

24:32.371 --> 24:34.788
Ma'am, they've found the president.

24:45.871 --> 24:49.038
(Graves coughing)

24:54.496 --> 24:57.038
That feels so good, right?

24:58.918 --> 25:00.210
Right?

25:00.996 --> 25:04.386
How'd I get this goddamn old

25:05.496 --> 25:07.955
and never really felt like this?

25:11.496 --> 25:12.996
It's never too late.

25:19.330 --> 25:21.662
Margaret: <i>Richard!</i>

25:21.663 --> 25:23.705
Richard!

25:26.663 --> 25:28.412
Good morning, sweetheart!

25:28.706 --> 25:30.829
Are you totally insane?

25:30.830 --> 25:33.829
No, no, dear, to the contrary.

25:33.830 --> 25:36.620
What are you doing? Get down here.

25:36.621 --> 25:39.662
Hey, look. Look at me.

25:39.663 --> 25:43.120
I'm free. I'm free from my old skin!

25:43.121 --> 25:45.995
Can you imagine
if anyone saw you like this?

25:45.996 --> 25:49.037
Oh, no, Maggie,
I'm through with imagining.

25:49.038 --> 25:50.620
I'm living now.

25:51.002 --> 25:52.954
It's never too late.

25:52.955 --> 25:55.787
I just crash-landed
in the middle of my life.

25:55.788 --> 25:57.662
Richard, enough.

25:57.663 --> 25:59.746
- Stop.
- <i>I'm born again, sweetheart,</i>

25:59.747 --> 26:02.495
and it's total peace.

26:02.907 --> 26:08.204
Which is the only thing I
really ever need anymore, Mags,

26:08.205 --> 26:12.287
is just a little motherfucking peace!

26:13.611 --> 26:15.244
Shit.

26:22.746 --> 26:24.203
You're angry.

26:25.121 --> 26:26.659
I'm confused,

26:27.580 --> 26:29.121
and not just about last night.

26:29.122 --> 26:31.620
What you did with your library...

26:31.621 --> 26:33.269
what were you thinking?

26:33.580 --> 26:36.454
Well, I wasn't thinking, Mags.

26:36.455 --> 26:37.913
For the first time in my life,

26:37.914 --> 26:39.912
I was just doing.

26:39.913 --> 26:42.288
Yeah, well, you scared
the hell out of me.

26:42.289 --> 26:45.175
You don't get to just
disappear like that.

26:45.746 --> 26:47.412
And then to find you...

26:47.413 --> 26:51.455
Oh, I'm sorry, Mags.
I'm really, really sorry.

26:57.205 --> 26:59.912
Anyway, the speech that you're giving

26:59.913 --> 27:02.038
this morning is very important.

27:02.039 --> 27:03.413
Mmm.

27:06.663 --> 27:08.205
What speech?

27:11.455 --> 27:13.538
Woman: <i>It's an honor to be here today</i>

27:13.539 --> 27:17.662
among so many survivors
in the fight against cancer.

27:17.663 --> 27:21.537
Now, all through my career,
I have devoted myself...

27:21.538 --> 27:23.170
Sorry, sorry.

27:23.171 --> 27:24.829
Mags, it's too tight.

27:24.830 --> 27:26.995
Oh, you big baby.

27:26.996 --> 27:30.246
Even though I didn't always
agree with his policies,

27:30.247 --> 27:33.162
Richard Graves is the very model

27:33.163 --> 27:36.162
of what a former president should be...

27:36.163 --> 27:37.752
a statesman.

27:37.915 --> 27:39.955
Oh, Jesus, I need a cigarette.

27:39.955 --> 27:41.829
Right before your kid's cancer speech?

27:41.830 --> 27:44.162
- Are you high?
- Yes.

27:44.163 --> 27:45.620
(Gasps)

27:45.621 --> 27:47.538
President Richard Graves.

27:59.288 --> 28:01.121
Mr. President.

28:17.371 --> 28:20.037
Thank you for that gracious welcome.

28:20.528 --> 28:24.705
Let me start by saying that when I look

28:24.705 --> 28:27.280
into these children's faces,

28:27.830 --> 28:30.829
I can feel their hurt and their pain

28:30.830 --> 28:32.991
now more than ever.

28:33.913 --> 28:35.600
(Sighs)

28:37.871 --> 28:39.621
Excuse me.

28:46.038 --> 28:48.829
I can only imagine the difficult

28:49.365 --> 28:52.495
and brave journey they've endured.

28:53.049 --> 28:54.602
The truth...

28:56.704 --> 28:58.956
the truth is that...

29:04.955 --> 29:06.704
Truth...

29:07.413 --> 29:08.792
uh...

29:10.080 --> 29:11.455
(no audible dialogue)

29:16.496 --> 29:17.929
I mean...

29:26.788 --> 29:27.961
The truth.

29:30.663 --> 29:32.089
The truth is,

29:32.746 --> 29:36.037
until we start forgiving ourselves

29:36.038 --> 29:39.079
for every bad decision we've ever made,

29:39.080 --> 29:41.995
we will be defined by our past

29:41.996 --> 29:44.454
and nothing will ever get done.

29:44.455 --> 29:45.829
What is he doing?

29:45.830 --> 29:47.037
That son of a...

29:47.038 --> 29:51.120
Look, this cancer thing, this disease,

29:51.121 --> 29:52.620
it's impossible.

29:52.621 --> 29:56.621
It's a moving target.
It evolves. It changes.

30:00.663 --> 30:03.639
But here's what I can tell you.

30:04.955 --> 30:09.954
It's all math, and they're scared of it.

30:10.136 --> 30:12.663
Your government is, your president is,

30:12.663 --> 30:14.162
your Congress is.

30:14.163 --> 30:17.121
Hell, I was. Scared shitless.

30:19.205 --> 30:20.455
I mean, let's face it.

30:20.456 --> 30:22.870
It was me who gutted

30:22.871 --> 30:26.080
the federal grants for cancer research.

30:26.913 --> 30:28.287
I did this.

30:28.657 --> 30:30.768
This has nothing to do
with what I wrote.

30:30.768 --> 30:32.329
I don't know how many people died

30:32.330 --> 30:35.245
because my political machine
at that time

30:35.246 --> 30:38.954
just figured,
"Hell, dying people don't vote."

30:38.955 --> 30:40.454
(crowd gasps)

30:41.017 --> 30:44.371
That's the dirty Washington calculus.

30:47.496 --> 30:49.080
Now, you want the truth?

30:50.788 --> 30:52.454
All right, your government spends

30:52.455 --> 30:56.368
about 4.5 billion on cancer research.

30:57.450 --> 31:00.412
Ladies and gentlemen, that is bullshit.

31:00.413 --> 31:03.120
That is just walking-around money.

31:03.121 --> 31:04.495
How about they take

31:04.496 --> 31:07.829
that $81 billion they plan on spending

31:07.830 --> 31:10.995
on new military aircraft next year

31:10.996 --> 31:14.704
and move it down to cancer research?

31:15.074 --> 31:19.330
You do that, and I guarantee you,
I promise you,

31:19.330 --> 31:21.995
we would have a cure for this disease

31:21.996 --> 31:23.829
within a decade.

31:23.830 --> 31:26.927
And I will help you get there,

31:28.411 --> 31:31.702
because I'm awake now.

31:31.830 --> 31:34.288
I'm wide awake.

31:35.996 --> 31:39.745
And I promise you, until the day I die,

31:39.746 --> 31:42.829
I will be your biggest advocate,

31:42.830 --> 31:44.620
your beacon of hope,

31:44.621 --> 31:46.996
your goddamn president!

32:03.913 --> 32:05.413
(No audible dialogue)

32:18.246 --> 32:20.788
You are such a brave little girl.

32:29.788 --> 32:32.079
"Black men enter here."

32:32.080 --> 32:34.205
- Oh, my God.
- He's a monster.

32:34.206 --> 32:37.163
God bless you.

